                            <comment id="437257" author="JIRAUSER18483" created="Tue, 3 Dec 2024 08:58:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve been thinking of that for a while, that&apos;s great you&apos;re doing it! While you&apos;re doing so, try to keep the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl TOPIC ACTION&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; approach, that would make it more ergonomic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you have some bandwidth, I was also thinking that a &quot;&lt;tt&gt;debug&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; topic could be introduced, and use that opportunity to rename some old commands:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lctl debug daemonlctl debug kernel (alias &apos;dk&apos;)lctl debug file (alias &apos;df&apos;)lctl debug clear (alias &apos;clear&apos;)lctl debug show (alias &apos;show&apos;)lctl debug list&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lctl debug filter (alias &apos;filter&apos;)lctl debug mark (alias &apos;mark&apos;)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Eventually we could deprecate some not very used aliases (filter and show?)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Aur&#233;lien&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
